      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That is a great idea, but I cannot recommend stopping warfarin or relying on high-dose garlic supplements to manage your blood thinning because doing so is extremely dangerous and could lead to life-threatening bleeding. Warfarin works by balancing your Vitamin K intake, and suddenly removing it or adding potent herbal supplements like garlic can cause your blood to clot or thin unpredictably, so you must stay on your prescribed medication and follow up with your doctor. Your doctor can help you explore safer alternatives, such as switching to apixaban or rivaroxaban, which are often more convenient and allow for a more varied diet without constant lab visits.",
